The paper proposes a novel population-based algorithm for black-box optimization, which is a common problem in the field of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The algorithm is tested on a benchmark proposed at the Congress on Evolutionary Computation, which is a conference focused on computational intelligence and evolutionary computation. The paper also applies the algorithm to train a Feedforward Neural Network, which is a common technique in the field of neural networks and deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
